# Git Conventions

## Commits (Conventional Commits)
Format: `<type>(<scope>): <description>`. Types: `feat`, `fix`, `refactor`, `test`, `docs`, `chore`, `perf`, `security`. Scopes (esempi): `api`, `auth`, `sessions`, `patients`, `paths`, `transcriptions`, `summaries`, `audio`, `notes`, `celery`, `integrations`, `specs`, `config`, `deps`, `infra`. Breaking: `feat(api)!: ...`.

Examples: `feat(sessions): add audio proxy upload URL`, `fix(auth): handle Cognito challenge`, `test(api): cover patient list pagination`.

## Branches
`<type>/<issue>-<short-desc>` e.g. `feat/12-session-transcription-status`.

## Pull requests
Conventional title; body `Closes #N` when applicable; squash to `main`; CI green when present; review per cambi non banali.

## Tooling
Conventional Commits sono la convenzione del team. Se in repo è presente Commitizen (`.cz.toml`), usare `cz commit`; altrimenti messaggi equivalenti a mano.
